{
  "source_translation": "The garden house in Hai Duong caused a stir in public opinion last May. Many news outlets reported that the son of Secretary Bui Thanh Quyen, Mr. Bui Thanh Tung, invested over 4 billion VND to acquire ownership of more than 4,000 square meters of land, including 500 square meters of aquaculture land converted to residential land without approval. Additionally, the Central Inspection Commission, which met from November 12-19 in Hanoi, stated that the use of 550 square meters of land for a water pond and rockery 'was not entirely in accordance with the intended use.' The Commission concluded: 'Upon review, there is no basis to conclude that comrade Bui Thanh Quyen intervened or directed relevant organizations or individuals in the procedures for transferring and changing land use for comrade Bui Thanh Tung...' 'However, comrade Bui Thanh Quyen needs to learn from this experience and seriously self-criticize for not regularly advising and educating his son to comply fully with land law regulations; not being decisive in allowing his son to buy and use land in Ninh Thanh, Ninh Giang, where some steps did not fully comply with regulations and procedures, causing negative public opinion and affecting personal and Party reputation.' The case of Mr. Bui Thanh Tung building a villa attracted public attention last May, and a National Assembly representative linked this issue to 'anti-corruption.' When the case appeared in the media, Mr. Bui Thanh Tung was serving as the Head of the Department...",
