{
  "source_translation": "The 47-year-old coach has requested to terminate his contract, which was set to remain in effect until 2018. \"It's not that I'm retiring; I haven't contacted any other clubs, but I have no plans to take a year off,\" he confirmed. Klopp has led Dortmund since 2008, guiding the team to two Bundesliga championships and reaching the Champions League final in 2012-13, but this season the team is currently in 10th place. They trail the top club, Bayern Munich, by 37 points. Klopp said at a press conference: \"I truly believe this is the right decision. This club deserves to be coached by someone who is 100% accurate.\" \"I have always said that when I believe I am no longer the perfect coach for this wonderful club, I will speak up.\" Regarded as one of the most talented coaches in Europe, the charismatic Klopp has led Dortmund to consecutive Bundesliga titles and became the first coach of Dortmund to achieve a domestic double. He also took the team to the Champions League final, a match at Wembley in England, where the team lost 2-1 to another German club, Bayern Munich. He is often mentioned as a candidate for clubs in the Premier League, including Manchester United before the team signed with him...",
