  "source_translation": "The S-400 air defense missile system was showcased during the Victory Day parade in Moscow on May 9. He also added that Ankara will collaborate with Moscow to produce the S-500 defense system, according to Reuters. Turkey has requested China to close its detention camps. A U.S. Navy aircraft fell into the sea, and the F-35 fighter jets saw combat for the first time. China is purchasing Russian aircraft to enhance its air force. U.S. officials commented that Turkey's plan to buy the S-400 missile defense system is a 'big issue' and stated that this deal could risk Ankara's contract to purchase F-35 fighter jets from Lockheed Martin Corp. However, Erdogan mentioned in a discussion with students in Istanbul that Turkey conducted a technical assessment, and the results showed that the 'incompatibility between the S-400 and F-35' that the U.S. is concerned about does not exist. Now, they (the Americans) are showing reluctance. But sooner or later, we will receive the F-35. The (U.S.) not delivering the fighter jets is not an option,' Erdogan said. The trade war is slowing down China's aircraft carrier construction. The West is sending sample ships to the South China Sea to counter China. In August 2018, military experts noted that China's air force would be strengthened in both quantity and capability as a series of Russian fighter jets were delivered to Beijing. At that time, the Russian government confirmed that 10 heavy, long-range, multi-role Su-35 fighter jets would be delivered to Beijing.",
