  "source_translation": "At the first-instance trial on August 16, lawyer Dang Dinh Manh stated that the appeal trial was conducted quickly. Mr. Luong, just like at the first-instance trial, was 'always very calm, extremely composed, gentle, almost always smiling, although he firmly denied the charges.' Notably, the court added a penalty prohibiting him from holding positions in state agencies and armed forces for five years. Mr. Luong's wife said, 'My husband is being falsely accused.' Mr. Luong received a 20-year sentence, the highest for activists. Lawyer Dai commented that the trial of Mr. Luong 'still holds many mysteries.' 'The very content of the additional penalty indicates the regime's intention towards him. Even in 20 years, he will be over 70 years old, which is not suitable for holding state or elected positions, but perhaps they still do not want that possibility to occur,' Mr. Manh said. 'In Vinh city, Mr. Luong is not well-known, but in Yen Thanh district, he is like a spiritual leader. He has done many beneficial things for the people, fighting against the government over local injustices. And that may have made him a thorn in the side of the authorities.' Mr. Manh noted that at the appeal trial this morning, hundreds of people from Mr. Luong's parish gathered at a street corner because 'they thought that since it was a public trial, they would be allowed to attend.' However, only his wife... ",
