{
  "source_translation": "The Su-30 aircraft produced by Russia (illustration) reported by local media, Major General Do Minh Tuan, Deputy Commander of the Air Defense-Air Force, stated that some ships and aircraft have been dispatched for rescue. However, he mentioned that 'there are no signs of the two pilots.' The Su-30 MK2 fighter jet formation of Regiment 923 took off on Tuesday morning, June 14, from Sao Vang Airport (Thọ Xuân - Thanh Hóa) for training exercises. One aircraft lost contact about 25 km from the mainland in Diễn Châu (Nghệ An). The military command of Nghệ An province reported that the last known position of the Su-30MK2 was to the east, about 6-7 km from Hon Mat Island, over 26 nautical miles from the mainland. Fisherman Le Van Cuong, who was fishing at sea, reported that at 8:30 AM the same day, fishermen discovered a plane crash in the sea at approximately 18-19 degrees north latitude, 106.4 degrees east longitude, about 4-6 nautical miles east of Mat Island (Cua Lo town, Nghệ An), according to Thanh Niên. It is known that the two pilots on the flight are Colonel Tran Quang Khai, Deputy Regiment Commander, Chief of Staff of Regiment 923, Division 371, and Major Nguyen Huu Cuong, Flight Leader. The Nghệ An sea area where the Su-30 MK2 is believed to have gone missing currently has three ships from Fleet 2 and ten fishing boats participating in the search for the missing aircraft. Regiment 923 has dispatched four rescue aircraft along with dozens of ships... ",
  "candidate_translation": "A Su-30MK2 aircraft went missing in Hà Niên, with Regiment 922 reporting it to the east."
